Built a new ASP.NET Core 8 + SQL Server backend aligned to the validated LCP-UML-3 model with 3NF tables, optimistic locking, and serializable write paths.

- Added full UML-mapped entities and DbContext (`LcpUml3.Api/Entities/Domain.cs`, `LcpUml3.Api/Data/HospitalContext.cs`), including TPT subtypes (Inpatient/Outpatient/EmergencyCase, Surgeon), FK graph per compositions, `RowVersion` `[Timestamp]` on all ghost-write–prone aggregates, and date/decimal precision.
- Implemented REST controllers: base data (`PatientsController`, `PatientRecordsController`, `LabOrdersController`, `RadiologyOrdersController`) plus critical, serializable + concurrency-protected write paths (`InpatientsController`, `OutpatientsController`, `EmergencyCasesController`, `LabResultsController`, `RadiologyImagesController`, `InsuranceClaimsController`, `BillingInvoicesController`) in `LcpUml3.Api/Controllers/*`.
- Defined 3NF SQL DDL with `rowversion` columns and FK constraints in `database/schema.sql`, matching the PlantUML keys and associations.
- Wired API host (`LcpUml3.Api/Program.cs`) and EF SQL Server deps (`LcpUml3.Api/LcpUml3.Api.csproj`, `appsettings.json`), plus usage notes in `src/README.md`.

Next steps:
1) Run `dotnet restore` (NuGet access needed) then `dotnet run` from `LcpUml3.Api`.
2) Apply `database/schema.sql` to your SQL Server/LocalDB before exercising endpoints.
3) Use Swagger at `/swagger` to verify the critical serializable endpoints return 409 on stale `RowVersion` updates.
